<strong>EDIT:</strong> Actually, the way it is implemented now, the algorithm can easily be defeated:<br />
<div style="color:Black;background-color:White;"><pre>
<span style="color:Blue;">int</span> limit = 8;
<span style="color:Blue;">double</span> h = 1.0 / limit;

<span style="color:Blue;">var</span> contour = <span style="color:Blue;">new</span> List&lt;Vertex&gt;() {
    <span style="color:Blue;">new</span> Vertex(0, 0), <span style="color:Blue;">new</span> Vertex(1, 0), <span style="color:Blue;">new</span> Vertex(h, h), <span style="color:Blue;">new</span> Vertex(0, 1)
};

<span style="color:Blue;">try</span>
{
    Contour.FindPointInPolygon(contour, limit);
}
<span style="color:Blue;">catch</span>
{
    Console.WriteLine(<span style="color:#A31515;">&quot;Failed.&quot;</span>);
}
</pre></div>The algorithm described in the above link (searching at a convex corner) might be a better option.<br />
